<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#000080">Originally posted by The Mystery Minstrel on 04-25-99 06:25 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Must.... Control.... Fist.... of.... Death....

Ok, so the flame board is that way. But this is ridiculous! What are you? The RP police? Should every poor bastard who goes out and buys the game be forced to read 3 or 4 complete series of fantasy books, play pen and paper RPG's 4 hours each night when they come home from work or school, and submit to an extended fantasy universe knowledge test just so they won't ANNOY you when they talk? In case you forgot, this game is on sale to the general public. To many, this is their first introduction into the fantasy universe. Cut them a little slack. In fact, I don't remember a single "thee" or "thou" coming from an NPC anywhere in the game, so if the developers don't think it's necessary, than why should you?

The only thing you should concern yourself with is the improper use of channels and blatantly improper names. Don't force everyone to RP and don't berate the attempts of others to RP a different way. IMHO the dwarf that responds, "Aya laddie," is still RP'ing. It's just their way of imagining what a dwarf would say.

Take the time and help these people out a little instead of slamming them. Show them how to properly roleplay if you must. Rather than berate them for bringing down your enjoyment, show them how better to enjoy it themselves. And don't get mad at the ones who don't want to play like you do. That's just plain being a snob.

If you don't like it, ignore it. Simple, eh?</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
